1
00:00:55,600 --> 00:01:00,276
THE WHORE AND THE WHALE

2
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:05,148
<i>Dear Lola...</i>

3
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,359
<i>I'm in Poblenou,
at a barricade.</i>

4
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:13,229
<i>After the battle of the Ebro the
Nationalists drove us into the sea.</i>

5
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:16,314
<i>They are crossing
the Llobregat</i>

6
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:18,750
<i>as I write to you,
quite pointlessly.</i>

7
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,910
<i>I could keep on running...</i>

8
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,550
<i>but the war has brought me
to your birthplace,</i>

9
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:25,670
<i>like returning home,</i>

10
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:28,316
<i>as if you were waiting for me.</i>

11
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:30,670
I liked your letter.

12
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:33,075
It's been a long time since
I got a love letter.

13
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:35,079
I didn't write it.

14
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:36,919
He did.

15
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:39,873
It's the same. You sent it to me.

16
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:44,154
How did you know
I was in Barcelona?

17
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,910
Everybody told me,
except you.

18
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:49,037
That you were staying
at your father's place...

19
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:51,231
with a son, and without a husband.

20
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:56,316
Don't look at him that way,
I'm starting to hate him.

21
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,635
Who was he?

22
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:52,316
An Argentine guy who died in Barcelona
when the nationalists arrived.

23
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:56,711
His pictures of the war
aren't bad, but...

24
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:59,996
these ones are a complete mystery.

25
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:02,999
Look.

26
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:07,229
We got them from a collector.

27
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:11,677
The letter came as part of the lot,
in his notebook.

28
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:16,036
And the pages of the letter,
did you tear them out?

29
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:19,152
No, they were loose, like this.
But he didn't mail it.

30
00:04:20,080 --> 00:04:21,195
Look.

31
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:33,990
- Have a good look.
- What?

32
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:37,919
She's exactly like you
were at her age.

33
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:43,389
<i>You escaped from me
until the very last night,</i>

34
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:46,712
<i>when the tour was over
and you were going back to Spain.</i>

35
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:50,791
<i>All of Buenos Aires
was at the farewell party.</i>

36
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:54,314
<i>I couldn't cope with it all,
handing over chorus girls,</i>

37
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:57,830
<i>but you... I saved for myself.</i>

38
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:02,869
<i>No one else in the company
undressed like you did.</i>

39
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:07,073
<i>As if it were a relief.
As if no one could hurt you.</i>

40
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,759
Lola!

41
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:11,833
<i>Nothing in this life
could scare you.</i>

42
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:15,077
<i>Not in this one,
nor in the other one either.</i>

43
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:16,429
I almost fell!

44
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:20,156
- You scared the life out of me!
- What were you going to do?

45
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,319
Kill myself...

46
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:26,708
- So they would all see.
- See you naked?

47
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:31,797
<i>If a photo can steal your soul,
I took yours that night.</i>

48
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:35,074
<i>Your memory is still intact,
motionless,</i>

49
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:38,751
<i>caught in that photo
like a fallen angel.</i>

50
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,913
Is that the woman in the letter?

51
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,793
I don't know,
she looks like a chorus girl.

52
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,356
There is a Dolores
in the program.

53
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,956
But the letter
could be for anyone.

54
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:58,116
Anyway. She's a character.

55
00:05:58,320 --> 00:06:02,029
Go to Argentina, investigate
that period and write about it.

56
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:14,835
Once...

57
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:20,112
at my convent, I took all my clothes
off in the confessional booth.

58
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,955
That day I finished
my primary education.

59
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:30,797
- How old were you?
- Fourteen.

60
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:35,518
I took my clothes off
and sang "Els Segadors".

61
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,708
<i>Bon colp de falc!</i>

62
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:42,709
Did you hear
the general's speech?

63
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:46,517
He toasted "the return of
the company to our Spain...

64
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:51,118
traditional Spain which has begun
to free itself from the reds".

65
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:53,038
I was taking photos of him.

66
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:57,317
You went upstairs as
if he'd insulted your mother.

67
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,953
My father.

68
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:05,829
Do you know why
the nuns threw me out?

69
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,878
Because my father burned
a church and they killed him.

70
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:16,710
They are my family.

71
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:21,190
Nobody else cares
if I leave or stay.

72
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,469
Me. I do.

73
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:29,310
You're going to Patagonia.

74
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:33,635
<i>You were the only one
who hadn't packed up.</i>

75
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,717
<i>You didn't want
to go back to Spain,</i>

76
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:38,195
<i>but didn't dare stay
on your own either.</i>

77
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:41,912
<i>You'd heard all the bullshit.</i>

78
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:44,271
Do you really care about me?

79
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:49,756
The truth is,
you saved my life.

80
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:53,756
You can do
what you like with me.

81
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:58,630
Don't sell your soul
to the devil.

82
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,915
Who said anything
about a soul?

83
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,873
<i>You did as you pleased,</i>

84
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:07,800
<i>without thinking of the price
you'd have to pay.</i>

85
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:12,752
<i>And whether you stay or go,
it's never for free.</i>

86
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:17,033
<i>And finding out what you want
doesn't come free either.</i>

87
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:19,071
- How long are you staying?
- Till Sunday.

88
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,918
On Monday I've got
to be back at work.

89
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,794
Writing silly articles
for a women's magazine.

90
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:27,149
I didn't send you this letter
just so I could see you, Vera.

91
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,112
I want you to publish.

92
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:33,155
By the age of 20 you had won
some award and published a novel.

93
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,515
That was then.

94
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:37,678
When you ran behind me picking up
the papers I'd thrown away.

95
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,831
The other day I mentioned
this book at dinner

96
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:49,554
and my father got up
from the table.

97
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,715
He's never read it,

98
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:55,798
but he couldn't stand
his patients praising it.

99
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,229
- It messed up my life, you know?
- Your father.

100
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,352
The book.

101
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,880
Are you sure you want me
to write another one?

102
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:12,353
That afternoon when you took this photo
of me fills an entire chapter.

103
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:16,194
And I didn't dare
write about all of it.

104
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:21,558
Many years have gone by.
Does it show?

105
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:23,912
What is it, Vera?

106
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:28,078
I have a lump here.
Feel it.

107
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:35,873
My sister is waiting to take me
to her gynecologist.

108
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:44,432
- Will you never ask me to stay?
- You have to go to the gynecologist.

109
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,030
Jordi!

110
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:49,155
The things you say, Vera.

111
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:50,914
When you left me for Antonio.

112
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,270
You see?
You don't understand anything.

113
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:55,232
That's why no woman will last
beyond the third fuck with you.

114
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:58,830
- I was with you for a year.
- Barely eleven months.

115
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:04,636
The happiest time of my life.

116
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:07,674
The only time when I didn't feel
alone in the whole world.

117
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:12,152
<i>- Digame'I en català.
- Et vaig estimar molt.</i>

118
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,759
Catalan...

119
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,879
That's the voice of my mother.
Her words.

120
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:21,878
I lie on my childhood bed and
her stories swirl round my head.

121
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,036
Do you lie on other beds?

122
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,679
Nobody's asked me to.

123
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:28,834
<i>Hello, Toni.</i>

124
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,792
<i>Sorry to interrupt
your meeting.</i>

125
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:34,995
<i>We're back in Madrid and I wanted
to make arrangements for Juanito.</i>

126
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:37,350
<i>- Where are you?
- In Avenida de America.</i>

127
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:40,957
There's loads of traffic...
Everybody's coming back to town.

128
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:48,828
The thing is... I won't be staying
at home, Antonio.

129
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:51,875
I also wanted to tell you that.

130
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:57,079
I don't know what my father said,
but I've made up my mind.

131
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,077
I've been thinking
about it all month.

132
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:01,999
It's better that I don't stay
at home, even for one night.

133
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:07,032
If Maribel's at home
I'll leave him with her.

134
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,073
I love you too.

135
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,678
Guess who's waiting
for you in the bathtub?

136
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:21,710
Pikachu.

137
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:27,309
Shall we give him a bath
while Maribel makes dinner?

138
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,274
And then later...

139
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:38,910
Remember we talked about mummy
not staying at home tonight?

140
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,712
Why?

141
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:44,272
I've already explained
it to you.

142
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:48,232
You know sometimes you do things
and you don't know why?

143
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:50,078
And then you tell me off.

144
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:55,476
I need to be alone, my love.
To find out what I want.

145
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,598
What do you want?

146
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,638
I don't know.

147
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:10,077
I don't want to get confused
by what my father wants for me.

148
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:12,556
Or grandpa, or whoever.

149
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:14,632
It's been the same all my life.

150
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:20,077
And now it's almost happening
again with your father.

151
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:25,113
<i>The train seemed to me
like a phantom ship,</i>

152
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:26,549
<i>adrift.</i>

153
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:32,195
<i>You would give in to whatever
happened without any impatience.</i>

154
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:36,672
<i>But I, who always want
what I haven't got,</i>

155
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,833
<i>counted out the minutes
like a prisoner.</i>

156
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:42,316
Don't you want
to make your wishes?

157
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,149
What wishes?

158
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:50,308
It's Cap d'an. New Year.

159
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:55,268
You eat a grape with each ring
of the bell and ask for what you want.

160
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:01,911
- Who are you missing tonight?
- Nobody.

161
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,989
Not even your family?

162
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:12,038
I really miss my uncle.

163
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:15,837
If my father met your uncle
he'd throw him in jail.

164
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:22,440
He hunts anarchists.

165
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:39,312
So you can really wish
for twelve things altogether?

166
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,995
I wish for everything I want.

167
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:48,716
It's twelve o'clock!

168
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:53,555
<i>I was afraid of you.</i>

169
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:56,791
<i>I can only admit</i>

170
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:59,393
<i>that now you're dead.</i>

171
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:03,429
<i>Your body scared me,
so full of life.</i>

172
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:07,835
Emilio, there are no grapes, but
there's wine, it's the same thing.

173
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:10,671
<i>And I find this hard
to admit but...</i>

174
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:14,833
<i>life separated us
more than death did.</i>

175
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:21,475
I want to always
fall in love like this.

176
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:24,839
With me.

177
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:30,593
With whoever!
With whom I choose.

178
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:33,231
With me.

179
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,439
I wish you would die for me.

180
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:42,754
May all my wishes come true.

181
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:45,790
It's no good saying "all".

182
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,911
You've got to say them
one by one.

183
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:04,231
If you don't cheat
the wish will come true.

184
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:24,318
Jordi!

185
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:28,517
I was dreaming.

186
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,952
You saved my life.

187
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:33,635
In a hotel.

188
00:15:34,680 --> 00:15:38,150
Last night. I took Juanito home
and called you.

189
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:42,837
I haven't felt this lonely
since my mother died.

190
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:47,038
I started typing on
her typewriter. Listen.

191
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:52,559
A blank page.

192
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:55,514
You can't read anything,
the ribbon's completely dry.

193
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:58,751
About that woman.

194
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:02,398
The one in the photos.
The one in the letter.

195
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:07,349
The letter from the photographer,
the guy you hate.

196
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:13,628
I was dreaming about him.
He was photographing me stark naked.

197
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:18,595
Just like that.
We're going to meet.

198
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,839
Excuse me. Hang on.

199
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,991
This thing about Argentina
is still on?

200
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,916
I'm going to leave
the magazine.

201
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:43,234
I don't have to think it over.
I'm not going to stay here.

202
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:46,311
Because I can't stand feeling
like shit just 100 meters away

203
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:48,909
from where my son is feeling
like shit, as if I were dead!

204
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,671
Last night I cried
more than he did.

205
00:16:57,440 --> 00:17:00,637
And if I think it over,
I'll end up agreeing with Antonio.

206
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,549
I'll be back home in three days.
It's better if I go.

207
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,118
As soon as possible.

208
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:12,190
Nothing.

209
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:16,394
Just see the gynecologist and have
a few tests. Three or four days.

210
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,431
The time it'll take you to send me
the ticket and the photos.

211
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:25,270
Thanks.

212
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:28,076
I'll do a good job,
you'll see.

213
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:59,556
<i>We wanted to get
to the end of the world.</i>

214
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,911
<i>There weren't even any roads.</i>

215
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:11,151
<i>When the gringo
landed at Bahía Blanca</i>

216
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:13,432
<i>we were already
about to board a ship.</i>

217
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:15,073
<i>He confirmed my first job.</i>

218
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:19,312
<i>It wasn't much money, but enough
for our trip to the south.</i>

219
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,994
<i>This Gringo Orestes was a peddler</i>

220
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:28,519
<i>who had a plane instead of a cart.</i>

221
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,912
<i>You got into that machine</i>

222
00:18:32,120 --> 00:18:35,317
<i>as if you'd always been
delivering stuff in Patagonia.</i>

223
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:50,514
<i>The town popped up,
in the middle of nowhere.</i>

224
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:54,638
<i>That first stop
promised a pleasant stay.</i>

225
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,560
<i>Easy work, bed, and food.</i>

226
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:07,676
<i>I had to take photos
for a musician...</i>

227
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,794
<i>to illustrate
the covers of his scores.</i>

228
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:17,518
<i>Nobody knew his name.</i>

229
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:21,755
<i>Even his son called him
by his surname: "Suárez".</i>

230
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:20,239
Gringo!
Did you bring the records?

231
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:22,631
Here we are, Suárez.
I got everything.

232
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:24,956
I've brought the photographer
and everything we'll need

233
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,388
for the great Radio El Mundo
tango competition.

234
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:27,919
Santamarina. Suárez.

235
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,792
El Pibe Pedro,

236
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:33,550
Bandoneon player
and future composer.

237
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:37,711
Emilio, right?
The Gringo speaks highly of you.

238
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:42,509
Did you come alone?

239
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:45,553
Dolores Puig.
A friend of Emilio's.

