I have to find a laboratory,

742
01:01:36,200 --> 01:01:37,872
make the copies,
talk to the printers...

743
01:01:38,080 --> 01:01:39,149
What if you never come back?

744
01:01:39,960 --> 01:01:41,678
How do I get back
to Buenos Aires?

745
01:01:47,200 --> 01:01:50,272
You're not free...
You're a coward.

746
01:01:50,480 --> 01:01:51,595
Gentlemen!

747
01:01:55,080 --> 01:01:56,957
I want to make a toast!

748
01:01:59,240 --> 01:02:00,434
To our friend,
the photographer.

749
01:02:00,640 --> 01:02:04,235
May he follow his destiny!
Cheers!

750
01:02:06,520 --> 01:02:09,637
Who knows what
marvels he will he find?

751
01:02:09,840 --> 01:02:12,638
But there's none better than
the one he's leaving behind.

752
01:02:12,840 --> 01:02:15,070
<i>I've always been intrigued
by her legend.</i>

753
01:02:15,960 --> 01:02:17,279
<i>What legend?</i>

754
01:02:17,560 --> 01:02:18,470
<i>Something they say</i>

755
01:02:18,680 --> 01:02:20,875
she did, which gave
the name to the tango.

756
01:02:22,720 --> 01:02:24,278
The light bulb.

757
01:02:29,040 --> 01:02:31,600
- That's it.
- What do you mean?

758
01:02:34,680 --> 01:02:36,272
Now it's nice and warm.

759
01:02:38,680 --> 01:02:40,079
Now I want you to play for me.

760
01:02:40,280 --> 01:02:41,474
<i>Apparently the first time</i>

761
01:02:41,680 --> 01:02:43,352
my grandfather played
this tango in public

762
01:02:43,560 --> 01:02:44,629
<i>she danced to it.</i>

763
01:02:47,040 --> 01:02:49,759
With a light bulb
stuck between her legs.

764
01:04:05,040 --> 01:04:08,112
Here's 500,
I'll send the rest as usual.

765
01:04:08,320 --> 01:04:09,196
Alright.

766
01:04:19,480 --> 01:04:22,677
When I came to study here
I lived at Matilde's place.

767
01:04:27,320 --> 01:04:29,550
I slept on the couch,
looking at that photo.

768
01:04:30,480 --> 01:04:32,118
A couple of times
I asked her about it,

769
01:04:32,320 --> 01:04:33,992
but she would get lost
in thought.

770
01:04:34,800 --> 01:04:37,030
She would just start
talking to herself.

771
01:04:37,560 --> 01:04:38,993
Poor old thing.

772
01:04:45,880 --> 01:04:48,110
- Where is this place?
- In Patagonia.

773
01:04:48,880 --> 01:04:50,916
What did you come
to Buenos Aires to study?

774
01:04:51,560 --> 01:04:54,313
Biology. Three years.

775
01:04:56,440 --> 01:04:58,112
Then I had to leave
and dropped out.

776
01:04:58,920 --> 01:05:01,229
In Mexico I used to take
tourists on scuba diving trips.

777
01:05:03,800 --> 01:05:06,155
Is it true you swim
with whales?

778
01:05:06,360 --> 01:05:08,078
I'm supposed
to only observe them.

779
01:05:10,280 --> 01:05:12,430
- I wouldn't like that...
- What?

780
01:05:12,840 --> 01:05:14,398
You just observing me.

781
01:05:16,160 --> 01:05:17,957
If I were a whale, I mean.

782
01:05:20,640 --> 01:05:22,232
What are you going
to do with all this?

783
01:05:23,400 --> 01:05:25,868
The lady asked me
to clear her room out.

784
01:05:29,720 --> 01:05:31,676
I have to go.
I'm going to miss my plane.

785
01:05:34,440 --> 01:05:36,112
Besides, if there's
something I can't stand,

786
01:05:36,760 --> 01:05:38,512
it's collecting memories.

787
01:05:39,840 --> 01:05:41,159
Is that so?

788
01:05:48,680 --> 01:05:50,477
And I don't like
farewells either.

789
01:05:51,920 --> 01:05:53,239
Be careful.

790
01:06:01,400 --> 01:06:03,436
Aren't you going to ask me
what they did to me?

791
01:06:03,840 --> 01:06:04,750
No.

792
01:06:07,640 --> 01:06:09,551
They removed a tumour
the size of a walnut...

793
01:06:09,760 --> 01:06:13,548
the left breast
and I don't know what else.

794
01:06:16,360 --> 01:06:18,191
The stitches
are still there...

795
01:06:19,640 --> 01:06:21,756
like barbed wire.

796
01:06:24,680 --> 01:06:27,274
- I wanted you to know.
- I knew.

797
01:06:28,520 --> 01:06:31,910
I could show you my heart.
Really...

798
01:06:34,000 --> 01:06:36,150
You can see it
between my ribs.

799
01:06:36,720 --> 01:06:38,233
The heartbeats.

800
01:07:28,440 --> 01:07:31,273
Here, a memento. Take anything
you like, but let's go.

801
01:07:33,360 --> 01:07:34,634
Anything?

802
01:07:44,160 --> 01:07:47,948
Go, then. Don't miss your flight.
I'll take care of everything.

803
01:07:50,240 --> 01:07:52,993
- I've already missed it.
- You can still make it.

804
01:07:53,200 --> 01:07:54,155
This is the peak season.

805
01:07:54,360 --> 01:07:56,669
They'll be starting
on the waiting list by now.

806
01:07:58,720 --> 01:08:00,073
Do you really mean it?

807
01:08:00,480 --> 01:08:03,040
I'd like to stay here
for a while, on my own.

808
01:08:06,600 --> 01:08:07,874
Really?

809
01:08:09,960 --> 01:08:12,110
I'll like to give you
something of mine.

810
01:08:18,240 --> 01:08:19,355
I wrote this.

811
01:08:20,880 --> 01:08:22,393
Seriously?

812
01:08:23,880 --> 01:08:26,678
This can't be you? Yes, it is,
when you were a girl!

813
01:08:27,480 --> 01:08:30,836
Look at this, you posed for
photos naked, just like...

814
01:08:32,040 --> 01:08:34,270
You really do look alike.
She wasn't far wrong, the old lady.

815
01:08:34,480 --> 01:08:35,674
Stop it!

816
01:08:36,080 --> 01:08:38,799
- So you were a writer.
- You said it: I was.

817
01:08:39,000 --> 01:08:41,036
- When I did what I wanted.
- Like what?

818
01:08:41,240 --> 01:08:43,196
I don't know, what I wanted.

819
01:08:45,160 --> 01:08:46,388
Like what?

820
01:08:47,200 --> 01:08:49,156
Like fucking a stranger.

821
01:09:08,200 --> 01:09:11,431
- Who is it?
- It's me, Suarez.

822
01:09:20,120 --> 01:09:22,953
Here. Take this.
Urondo's token.

823
01:09:24,040 --> 01:09:25,155
Take it!

824
01:09:56,280 --> 01:09:59,431
<i>The plane went out over the sea
and we flew over the beacon.</i>

825
01:10:00,440 --> 01:10:03,193
<i>The tide was high
and the whale had gone.</i>

826
01:10:04,840 --> 01:10:07,115
<i>I had a weird feeling,
one of relief,</i>

827
01:10:07,600 --> 01:10:09,716
<i>that stayed with me
for the rest of the journey.</i>

828
01:10:10,840 --> 01:10:13,638
<i>As if everything
had fallen into place.</i>

829
01:10:21,480 --> 01:10:24,438
<i>This morning a whale was stranded
on the shores of Patagonia.</i>

830
01:10:24,640 --> 01:10:27,757
<i>- Here's the story.
- For reasons we are not aware</i>

831
01:10:27,960 --> 01:10:31,873
<i>this 15 metre-long adult
whale was stranded.</i>

832
01:10:32,080 --> 01:10:33,672
<i>Apparently it's a female.</i>

833
01:10:33,880 --> 01:10:37,668
<i>We are working with volunteers
and staff from the institute</i>

834
01:10:37,880 --> 01:10:39,791
<i>in an effort to keep it alive.</i>

835
01:10:40,280 --> 01:10:43,989
<i>And we're hoping that at high tide
it might free itself naturally.</i>

836
01:10:45,120 --> 01:10:47,918
<i>Thanks to our colleagues
at Puerto Madryn TV</i>

837
01:10:48,120 --> 01:10:49,439
<i>for this coverage...</i>

838
01:11:20,040 --> 01:11:22,952
- What are you doing here?
- I called the Institute.

839
01:11:23,800 --> 01:11:25,233
They told me you were
with the whale.

840
01:11:25,440 --> 01:11:27,476
That you'd be back here
when it got dark.

841
01:11:28,120 --> 01:11:29,758
When I saw that
it was stranded again...

842
01:11:30,200 --> 01:11:31,792
It was stranded again?

843
01:11:32,000 --> 01:11:35,231
That a whale was stranded
again on the same spot.

844
01:11:37,040 --> 01:11:39,554
- What was that?
- Whales.

845
01:11:39,760 --> 01:11:43,150
Mating. This place
is perfect for mating.

846
01:11:44,440 --> 01:11:45,759
The Seal. This is Vera.

847
01:11:45,960 --> 01:11:48,155
- Hello, Seal.
- Hello, Vera.

848
01:11:49,680 --> 01:11:52,672
I guess I also came
to see you again.

849
01:11:53,520 --> 01:11:56,671
I'm sorry, it's not my fault.
Somebody called me.

850
01:11:57,360 --> 01:11:58,918
Well... me.

851
01:11:59,680 --> 01:12:01,750
It seems to make
no sense to you?

852
01:12:02,600 --> 01:12:04,716
But it's like the boy
in your story,

853
01:12:04,920 --> 01:12:06,831
we can't really
understand much.

854
01:12:08,680 --> 01:12:10,910
The same happened
to me with Matilde.

855
01:12:13,120 --> 01:12:17,113
I felt I was being called
and went up to say goodbye.

856
01:12:19,600 --> 01:12:21,830
I thought it was me
who was leaving.

857
01:12:26,520 --> 01:12:28,112
Do you have any rooms free?

858
01:12:29,760 --> 01:12:32,274
- How's the whale?
- Still alive.

859
01:12:33,160 --> 01:12:34,434
It's under the beacon
on the cliff.

860
01:12:34,640 --> 01:12:36,949
Wasn't the one with
the harpoon over there?

861
01:12:37,160 --> 01:12:40,391
- Somewhere around there.
- Where did it have the harpoon?

862
01:12:40,760 --> 01:12:43,194
Stuck right here.
Behind the eye.

863
01:12:43,560 --> 01:12:45,755
I'm sorry, madam,
we have no rooms left.

864
01:12:45,960 --> 01:12:47,916
She can have mine.
I'll sleep on the boat.

865
01:12:48,120 --> 01:12:51,192
- You're crazy. You can't.
- It's yours.

866
01:12:58,440 --> 01:13:00,829
The whale you mentioned,
the one with the harpoon,

867
01:13:01,480 --> 01:13:04,040
- was that many years ago?
- It was 1934.

868
01:13:05,360 --> 01:13:06,998
A long time ago...

869
01:13:10,760 --> 01:13:12,637
Could it be the same whale?

870
01:13:13,120 --> 01:13:15,315
She'd have to be very old.

871
01:13:23,960 --> 01:13:25,598
What do I do with this?

872
01:13:26,200 --> 01:13:28,077
I don't know.
He sent it to you.

873
01:13:29,080 --> 01:13:31,640
Didn't he give you anything else?
No letter?

874
01:13:32,680 --> 01:13:34,432
He sent the scores for Suarez.

875
01:13:34,640 --> 01:13:36,915
And he asked me to give you one
as a souvenir, that's all.

876
01:13:41,520 --> 01:13:45,149
You can't work like this.
Aren't you taking anything?

877
01:13:47,680 --> 01:13:49,750
When I get back
I'll bring you some medicine.

878
01:13:51,320 --> 01:13:52,230
Where was Emilio going?

879
01:13:52,440 --> 01:13:55,079
He was on his way south,
to Puerto Deseado.

880
01:13:56,120 --> 01:13:57,917
He was going to take a ship
for Tierra del Fuego.

881
01:14:00,000 --> 01:14:02,753
Suarez owes me money. It's yours
if you can get me out of here.

882
01:14:04,720 --> 01:14:07,518
I could hide in the plane.
Nobody will know.

883
01:14:08,480 --> 01:14:10,516
And afterwards?
How could I come back?

884
01:14:11,320 --> 01:14:12,833
I have to work here.

885
01:14:20,360 --> 01:14:21,952
Take care of that cold of yours.

886
01:14:23,480 --> 01:14:26,040
<i>The Gringo Orestes had the habit
of talking to himself.</i>

887
01:14:28,040 --> 01:14:29,837
<i>Once he told me
that forgotten words</i>

888
01:14:30,040 --> 01:14:31,758
<i>could still be heard
in the air.</i>

889
01:14:32,600 --> 01:14:36,149
<i>That if you repeated them,
the same things would happen again.</i>

890
01:14:37,400 --> 01:14:38,753
<i>I'm writing this,</i>

891
01:14:38,960 --> 01:14:42,919
<i>the things I never told you,
in case that's true.</i>

892
01:14:48,680 --> 01:14:50,557
When these photos were taken

893
01:14:50,760 --> 01:14:52,637
they didn't think
about identifying them.

894
01:14:54,240 --> 01:14:55,639
Look...

895
01:14:56,760 --> 01:14:58,671
..the calluses are the same.

896
01:14:59,720 --> 01:15:01,631
Your hunch is not so absurd.

897
01:15:01,840 --> 01:15:04,308
Scientists don't believe
in these things?

898
01:15:04,520 --> 01:15:05,509
On the contrary.

899
01:15:06,080 --> 01:15:07,798
That's what we do.

900
01:15:09,800 --> 01:15:12,314
Last night I dropped by
but I couldn't find you.

901
01:15:13,320 --> 01:15:15,231
Do you always write at night?

902
01:15:17,040 --> 01:15:19,998
- It's been ages since I wrote.
- You got inspired.

903
01:15:21,360 --> 01:15:23,828
This place is ideal for that too.

904
01:15:24,160 --> 01:15:26,151
They say you just
have to get started.

905
01:15:27,720 --> 01:15:31,349
The problem is, if it doesn't
come out, it rots inside.

906
01:15:38,440 --> 01:15:40,476
Each of these represented
a pile of money.

907
01:15:40,680 --> 01:15:42,750
They made combs,
nitro glycerine,

908
01:15:42,960 --> 01:15:44,757
oils, all sorts of stuff.

909
01:15:45,240 --> 01:15:48,357
- How long can it hold out?
- Probably, until another tide.

910
01:15:49,360 --> 01:15:51,510
There isn't much we can do.

911
01:15:51,840 --> 01:15:55,515
Keep her wet, and scare the fucking
seagulls hurting her.

912
01:15:56,840 --> 01:15:59,957
It's sink or swim. If she doesn't
free herself nobody else can.

913
01:16:08,120 --> 01:16:09,997
And what if it
was the same one?

914
01:16:10,200 --> 01:16:13,476
I don't know, perhaps
it would be of scientific interest.

915
01:16:13,680 --> 01:16:17,150
You win, Gallega.
It has a scar behind the eye.

916
01:16:17,360 --> 01:16:19,351
Did you hear?

917
01:16:20,280 --> 01:16:22,555
How did you get
in this mess, old lady?

918
01:16:23,160 --> 01:16:25,071
What did you come back for?

919
01:16:25,280 --> 01:16:26,952
I started reading your book
on the plane.

920
01:16:27,160 --> 01:16:28,559
- Did you?
- I liked it.

921
01:16:29,600 --> 01:16:32,034
- I like the girl's freedom.
- Really?

922
01:16:33,960 --> 01:16:35,916
Would you have liked to meet her?

923
01:16:39,360 --> 01:16:40,952
You left a letter inside.

924
01:16:44,880 --> 01:16:47,553
- Did you read it?
- Of course not.

925
01:16:48,680 --> 01:16:50,557
I've read it a thousand times.

926
01:16:50,760 --> 01:16:53,957
And instead of text for a book of
photos, I wrote something else.

927
01:16:54,560 --> 01:16:57,438
I put myself in Lola's place.
She wasn't afraid of anything.

928
01:16:57,640 --> 01:16:58,868
But how do you know?

929
01:16:59,440 --> 01:17:02,318
I know. I can imagine her.

930
01:17:02,760 --> 01:17:05,320
I write about her as
if I was writing about myself.

931
01:17:06,840 --> 01:17:08,956
And you haven't written
anything else until now?

932
01:17:09,320 --> 01:17:10,116
No.

933
01:17:10,680 --> 01:17:12,716
After publishing the novel
I got married...

934
01:17:14,120 --> 01:17:15,314
and had a son.

935
01:17:17,160 --> 01:17:19,230
- Do you have children?
- Yes.

936
01:17:20,360 --> 01:17:23,955
A nine year old girl who lives
with her mother in Mexico.

937
01:17:26,680 --> 01:17:28,398
And can you bear
being away from her?

938
01:17:29,600 --> 01:17:30,715
No.

939
01:17:31,080 --> 01:17:33,196
Then you know how much it hurts.

940
01:17:38,920 --> 01:17:41,593
You didn't really come to write
a book on whales, did you?

941
01:17:42,560 --> 01:17:44,630
Didn't Matilde ever mention
a photographer?

942
01:17:44,840 --> 01:17:46,876
Yes, the one who did
the photos for the scores.

943
01:17:47,080 --> 01:17:49,548
I've got his photos,
and the letter.

944
01:17:49,760 --> 01:17:53,548
He wrote it to Lola the day
before he died, in January '39.

945
01:17:57,200 --> 01:17:59,668
- He never sent it?
- He was killed in the war.

946
01:18:00,840 --> 01:18:04,628
But Lola was dead already.
I came here to investigate that.

947
01:18:10,040 --> 01:18:12,349
- What do you know about Lola?
- Nothing.

948
01:18:12,800 --> 01:18:14,153
Just what my grandfather told me.

949
01:18:14,360 --> 01:18:16,396
That she went back to Spain
and became a star.

950
01:18:16,600 --> 01:18:17,316
That's not true.

951
01:18:17,840 --> 01:18:19,990
If Lola worked for him,
there's no way he wouldn't see.

952
01:18:20,440 --> 01:18:22,749
My grandfather was blind, Vera.

953
01:18:25,880 --> 01:18:27,996
What you wrote
is related to these photos?

954
01:18:31,000 --> 01:18:33,594
Did you already have them
when Matilde left you the photo?

955
01:18:33,800 --> 01:18:35,199
They belong to
a publishing house.

956
01:18:35,400 --> 01:18:37,755
It's publishing a book of photos.
They want me to write the text.

957
01:18:37,960 --> 01:18:39,313
Why didn't you tell me?

958
01:18:40,640 --> 01:18:43,359
I don't know.
I'm sorry.

959
01:18:43,960 --> 01:18:47,555
I was about to return to Madrid,
empty handed, as I'd found nothing,

960
01:18:47,760 --> 01:18:50,479
I was operated on in Buenos Aires
and I met Matilde.

961
01:18:51,160 --> 01:18:52,593
Chance, destiny,
call it what you like.

962
01:18:52,800 --> 01:18:54,711
I took you to her nursing home.
It wasn't destiny.

963
01:18:55,280 --> 01:18:57,396
You screwed me and you kept
Matilde's stuff.

964
01:18:57,600 --> 01:18:58,794
That's not chance.

965
01:18:59,000 --> 01:19:01,230
Anyway, you were going
to throw everything out.

966
01:19:06,400 --> 01:19:07,389
Hello!

967
01:19:09,080 --> 01:19:10,399
What are you doing here?

968
01:19:10,840 --> 01:19:12,717
Nothing, just passing by.

969
01:19:13,640 --> 01:19:16,029
If you still have any complaints,
this is the editor of the book.

970
01:19:16,240 --> 01:19:18,708
Jordi Ferré.
He'll take care of everything.

971
01:19:19,080 --> 01:19:20,832
I forgot your name.

972
01:19:21,160 --> 01:19:22,115
Ernesto Suárez.

973
01:19:22,320 --> 01:19:24,231
The grandson of the guy
who exploited Lola.

974
01:19:24,440 --> 01:19:26,476
- Who?
- Lola, Jordi.

975
01:19:26,680 --> 01:19:28,318
The one in the letter.

976
01:19:29,720 --> 01:19:30,914
Hello, Ernesto.

977
01:19:32,000 --> 01:19:34,833
- How did you find me?
- Where do you want me to start?

978
01:19:35,040 --> 01:19:36,678
From where you betrayed me
to Antonio.

979
01:19:36,880 --> 01:19:39,075
After that I called Dr. Zimmerman,
I flew to Madrid,

980
01:19:39,280 --> 01:19:41,271
from there to Buenos Aires,
went to the hospital to see him,

981
01:19:41,480 --> 01:19:43,994
then to your hotel and you'd left.
A two hour flight to Puerto Madryn...

982
