You sold me as a whore.

1225
01:42:12,600 --> 01:42:14,670
- I didn't say that.
- Don't you touch me!

1226
01:42:30,760 --> 01:42:32,830
Do you know what I wondered
when I was far away?

1227
01:42:37,320 --> 01:42:38,594
Who are you

1228
01:42:42,200 --> 01:42:44,077
when nobody's looking at you?

1229
01:43:05,480 --> 01:43:08,199
We're going to take
Matilde out to sea.

1230
01:43:09,680 --> 01:43:11,432
Ernesto's asking
if you want to come with us.

1231
01:43:13,440 --> 01:43:16,079
- I got you out of bed.
- No way.

1232
01:43:17,000 --> 01:43:19,753
I was writing.
I think I found it.

1233
01:43:20,560 --> 01:43:22,516
- Your novel?
- Yes.

1234
01:43:23,240 --> 01:43:25,231
And when your father
called at my door...

1235
01:43:25,440 --> 01:43:28,034
I thought he was going to tell me
the whale had gone.

1236
01:43:28,240 --> 01:43:29,036
Another hunch?

1237
01:43:29,240 --> 01:43:31,834
Or better still,
that she'd gone again.

1238
01:43:33,280 --> 01:43:37,398
- Shall we go and see?
- Why not? We're going that way.

1239
01:43:44,000 --> 01:43:45,399
<i>You slept a while,</i>

1240
01:43:46,200 --> 01:43:48,475
<i>and I stayed looking at you
for the rest of the night.</i>

1241
01:43:54,880 --> 01:43:58,156
<i>When Pibe Pedro knocked on
he door to take us to the plane,</i>

1242
01:44:00,240 --> 01:44:02,913
<i>you opened your eyes and looked
at me as if I were a stranger.</i>

1243
01:44:33,640 --> 01:44:35,835
<i>As dawn was breaking
and we took off,</i>

1244
01:44:36,440 --> 01:44:39,159
<i>I could see the whale
near the sandbar.</i>

1245
01:44:39,960 --> 01:44:43,236
<i>With the sure instinct of animals,
as if time didn't exist,</i>

1246
01:44:44,760 --> 01:44:47,228
<i>it headed for a specific spot
in the middle of the sea.</i>

1247
01:45:24,800 --> 01:45:27,189
I'm worth more
than 1,500 pesos.

1248
01:45:28,040 --> 01:45:29,837
Listen, you. Don't be stupid!

1249
01:45:32,200 --> 01:45:34,430
Don't mistake value for price.

1250
01:45:40,520 --> 01:45:42,670
I'm not free because
they let me go.

1251
01:45:42,880 --> 01:45:45,997
I'm free because
I was born that way.

1252
01:45:46,280 --> 01:45:47,838
Even though
I've only been here

1253
01:45:48,040 --> 01:45:50,554
for other people's pleasure.
Isn't that right Suarez?

1254
01:45:57,560 --> 01:45:59,471
You really saw through me...

1255
01:46:04,280 --> 01:46:06,635
even if you're a blind bastard.

1256
01:46:08,880 --> 01:46:10,438
Beat it, girl.

1257
01:47:21,840 --> 01:47:25,196
- And now what?
- I told Seal to follow the whale.

1258
01:47:25,600 --> 01:47:26,635
You tell me where to stop...

1259
01:47:26,840 --> 01:47:28,751
And we'll throw the ashes
into the water,

1260
01:47:29,760 --> 01:47:30,749
alright?

1261
01:47:32,480 --> 01:47:35,517
I'll throw you in,
if you don't tell me the story.

1262
01:47:49,600 --> 01:47:51,272
I didn't even tell Suarez.

1263
01:47:52,000 --> 01:47:53,797
You're Suarez now.

1264
01:47:54,000 --> 01:47:56,912
You're no longer a boy, pops.
And me neither.

1265
01:48:11,760 --> 01:48:14,035
My old man never tells.

1266
01:48:14,920 --> 01:48:16,751
He's been like that all his life.

1267
01:48:21,760 --> 01:48:24,228
When my grandfather
told his stories...

1268
01:48:24,440 --> 01:48:26,237
my dad would leave so
as not to have listen to them.

1269
01:48:31,240 --> 01:48:32,798
Do you feel okay, Gallega?

1270
01:48:34,680 --> 01:48:36,557
You shouldn't be doing this.

1271
01:48:37,960 --> 01:48:39,029
Take your clothes off,
so you don't get...

1272
01:48:39,240 --> 01:48:41,310
I can do as I please!
Don't treat me like I was ill.

1273
01:48:41,520 --> 01:48:45,195
But you are ill. I forget too
at times, but you're ill.

1274
01:48:46,560 --> 01:48:47,834
I'm okay.

1275
01:48:48,600 --> 01:48:49,715
I'm just a little dizzy.

1276
01:48:52,400 --> 01:48:55,790
It's not my fault.
Some things just happen.

1277
01:49:21,000 --> 01:49:23,116
Forgive me.
I don't know what I'm saying.

1278
01:49:23,320 --> 01:49:25,914
Say whatever you like...

1279
01:49:27,880 --> 01:49:29,472
but don't say you're sorry.

1280
01:49:48,360 --> 01:49:50,590
Today your father
reminded me of mine.

1281
01:49:54,560 --> 01:49:56,516
All the things
we never said to each other.

1282
01:49:59,880 --> 01:50:02,633
All my life I've blamed him
for everything.

1283
01:50:11,960 --> 01:50:14,110
What you say is true.

1284
01:50:15,920 --> 01:50:17,592
Of course I'm ill.

1285
01:50:19,240 --> 01:50:21,470
It's a relief
to hear you say it.

1286
01:51:01,440 --> 01:51:05,069
I don't know what you were
like before. But you're beautiful.

1287
01:51:31,400 --> 01:51:34,233
So you're leaving
tomorrow morning.

1288
01:51:34,440 --> 01:51:36,317
I do as I please.

1289
01:51:39,320 --> 01:51:42,118
Like Lola, she finally
finds out what she wants.

1290
01:51:44,240 --> 01:51:47,516
One day I'll find
your novel in a bookstore,

1291
01:51:48,480 --> 01:51:50,232
and I'll know you're okay.

1292
01:51:50,680 --> 01:51:53,240
- Will you buy it?
- Yes.

1293
01:51:54,560 --> 01:51:57,313
- And will you read it?
- Yes.

1294
01:51:59,720 --> 01:52:01,756
Then I'll write it.

1295
01:52:27,200 --> 01:52:28,519
Is it here?

1296
01:52:30,520 --> 01:52:32,317
The airstrip was over there.

1297
01:52:35,280 --> 01:52:37,669
They came this way...

1298
01:52:38,120 --> 01:52:40,714
and circled over the whales.

1299
01:52:44,240 --> 01:52:46,037
<i>We stayed over there.</i>

1300
01:53:23,440 --> 01:53:24,839
Whales!

1301
01:54:24,640 --> 01:54:25,629
Lola!

1302
01:54:29,560 --> 01:54:31,118
Give me your hand.

1303
01:54:31,320 --> 01:54:33,038
Give me your hand!

1304
01:54:36,640 --> 01:54:38,312
Gringo! Level the plane!

1305
01:54:41,080 --> 01:54:42,672
Gringo!

1306
01:54:42,880 --> 01:54:45,189
Level it, God damn it!
Lola!

1307
01:54:45,680 --> 01:54:49,434
Take a photo of me!
Take a photo of me!

1308
01:55:33,880 --> 01:55:36,269
<i>And then the plane
went on with its journey.</i>

1309
01:55:37,640 --> 01:55:38,834
<i>And the Gringo...</i>

1310
01:55:40,720 --> 01:55:42,119
never came back.

1311
01:55:45,520 --> 01:55:48,273
- Can you still see them?
- Yes...

1312
01:55:52,760 --> 01:55:55,513
They're making circles
above the whales.

1313
01:56:02,160 --> 01:56:04,720
After some time Matilde
started telling me...

1314
01:56:06,120 --> 01:56:08,270
that I'd made all this up.

1315
01:56:12,040 --> 01:56:14,793
And that if I ever told Suarez...

1316
01:56:17,160 --> 01:56:19,913
She'd say I'm a liar.

1317
01:56:29,800 --> 01:56:30,994
And Suarez...

1318
01:56:33,320 --> 01:56:34,878
never found out.

1319
01:58:03,040 --> 01:58:04,678
<i>I can hardly see
what I'm writing.</i>

1320
01:58:05,920 --> 01:58:07,911
<i>Bullets are falling
like shooting stars.</i>

1321
01:58:08,120 --> 01:58:10,315
<i>And I make the same wishes
as I always did.</i>

1322
01:58:14,680 --> 01:58:17,513
<i>Here, at war, while I wait
for my turn to come</i>

1323
01:58:18,560 --> 01:58:20,551
<i>I take pictures of death
every day.</i>

1324
01:58:21,320 --> 01:58:25,359
<i>She's playing hard to get because
she knows I'm waiting for her.</i>

1325
01:58:26,400 --> 01:58:28,231
<i>Be patient.</i>

1326
01:58:29,800 --> 01:58:31,392
<i>I won't be long.</i>

1327
